Web Consortium’s (W3C) Hyper Text Markup Language (HTML) 5 and Cascading Style Sheets (CSS).&nbsp; The website was built in compliance with the accessibility standards established by section 508 of discovered to be inaccessible, please report it using the above link and we will ensure that the issue is addressed.</p>\n<p style=\"font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: class=\"banner-text\">\n      \n          Your Summer, Your Pace    </div>\n    </div>\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n</div>\n    \n      </div>\n    </div>\n</header>\n\n<main class=\"row clearfix\">\n </div>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"t27-intro-box\" class=\"l-intro-box clearfix row\"> <!-- this needs to go back at some point - not clear whether video goes here or not  id=\"video-toggle-below\" -->\n  <div class=\" left-27 column small-12 medium-9\">\n    <p>Registration will open February 6, 2017! Whatever your interest, Pace has a program to meet your needs. Summer Sessions start on May 16 and July 12.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</div><!-- / .l-intro-box --> \n\n<div class=\"m-admissions-group row\">\n  <ul class=\"clearfix\">\n\n              <li class=\"green\">\n                  <a href=\"http://www.pace.edu/admission-aid/summer/current-students\">\n                    <div class=\"img-container\">\n            <img typeof=\"foaf:Image\" src=\"http://www.pace.edu/sites/default/files/styles/t27_feature_image/public/summer-session-current-students_0.jpg?itok=bR4f8B7Q\" width=\"310\" height=\"240\" alt=\"Summer Session, Current Pace Students\">                          <div class=\"loc-info\">\n                <p>Enroll in the 2017 Summer Session and Finish in Four! With more than 600 classes to choose from, you can catch up and graduate faster.</p>\n              </div>\n                      </div>\n                      <div class=\"location-info\">\n                  <a name=\"main-content\"></a>\n                  \t\t    <img src=\"/sites/all/themes/volunteermatch/images/webinar_icon.png\" class=\"webinar-icon\"><h1 class=\"title\" id=\"page-title\">Nonprofit Insights: Greg Baldwin Shares Common Challenges in Screening Volunteers</h1>\n                                                        \n<div id=\"block-block-3\" class=\"block block-block first odd\">\n\n      \n  <h3>Attend this live webinar!</h3>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<article class=\"node-581 node node-webinar view-mode-full clearfix\" about=\"/webinars/nonprofit-insights-greg-baldwin-shares-common-challenges-screening-volunteers\" typeof=\"sioc:Item foaf:Document\">\n\n      <header>\n                  <span property=\"dc:title\" content=\"Nonprofit Insights: Greg Baldwin Shares Common Challenges in Screening Volunteers\" class=\"rdf-meta element-hidden\"></span><span property=\"sioc:num_replies\" content=\"0\" datatype=\"xsd:integer\" class=\"rdf-meta element-hidden\"></span>\n      \n          </header>\n  \n  <div id=\"maininforight\">\n<div class=\"web-reg\"><h3>Upcoming Dates</h3>\n<div class=\"web-reg-date\"><span class=\"date-display-single\" property=\"dc:date\" datatype=\"xsd:dateTime\" content=\"2017-04-27T11:00:00-07:00\">Thursday, April 27, 2017</span><br>\n<span class=\"web-reg-time\">11:00am - 12:00pm Pacific / 2:00pm - 3:00pm Eastern</span></div>\n<div class=\"web-reg-link\"><a href=\"https://attendee.gotowebinar.com/register/5671397906306601474\">Click Here To Register</a></div>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"field field-name-field-duration field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=\"field-label\">Duration:&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\">60 minutes</div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-field-topic field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=\"field-label\">Topic:&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\"><a href=\"/training-topics/nonprofit-insights-webinar-series\" typeof=\"skos:Concept\" property=\"rdfs:label skos:prefLabel\" datatype=\"\">Nonprofit Insights Webinar Series</a></div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-field-facilitators field-type-entityreference field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=\"field-label\">Facilitator(s):&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\"><a href=\"/facilitators/greg-baldwin\">Greg Baldwin</a></div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-field-hosted-by field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=\"field-label\">Hosted By:&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\">VolunteerMatch</div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-field-cost field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=\"field-label\">Cost:&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\">Free</div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\" property=\"content:encoded\"><p>What role do background screens play in overall risk management for your organization? Who pays for them and for which roles? How do volunteers feel about being screened? And are all “background check” services created equal?</p>\n<p>In this Q&amp;A-style webinar, VolunteerMatch President Greg Baldwin will address common challenges nonprofits face when screening volunteers — including boardroom discussions, implementing new processes, value vs. cost, and gaps in traditional background screens that increase vulnerability, or worse yet, threaten your community.</p>\n<p>We’ll invite attendees to submit their questions about screening practices and identify best practices for verifying identity and checking criminal records. Greg will share detailed results from two surveys recently facilitated by VolunteerMatch on the topic of background screening practices.</p>\n<p>In the survey we sent nonprofits, for example, more than 30% said they don’t currently run criminal or background screens, yet more than 90% of volunteers feel positively about participating in the screening process. We’re talking about screening volunteers and want to keep the conversation going because avoiding these conversations can come at a cost. Better screening practices lead to a healthy nonprofit sector, letting you focus on what you enjoy doing most — changing our world by engaging volunteers.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"field field-name-field-learn field-type-text-long field-label-above\"><div class=\"field-label\">What You'll Learn:&nbsp;</div><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\"><p>● Understanding common challenges nonprofits face when screening volunteers.</p>\n<p>● How nonprofits and volunteers across America feel about identity assurance.</p>\n<p>● What makes a great background check (and what doesn’t) along with new solutions for nonprofit screening practices.</p></div></div></div><!--\nTHIS FILE IS NOT USED AND IS HERE AS A STARTING POINT FOR CUSTOMIZATION ONLY.\nSee http://api.drupal.org/api/function/theme_field/7 for details.\nAfter copying this file to your theme's folder and customizing it, remove this\nHTML comment.\n-->\n<div class=\"field class=\"views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first views-row-last\">\n      \n  <div class=\"views-field views-field-field-facilitator-photo\">        <div class=\"field-content\"><a href=\"/facilitators/greg-baldwin\"><img typeof=\"foaf:Image\" src=\"http://learn.volunteermatch.org/sites/default/files/styles/100square/public/facilitators/baldy.jpg?itok=zauMJPUP\" width=\"100\" </div>  \n  <div class=\"views-field views-field-field-teaser\">        <div class=\"field-content\">Greg Baldwin is the President of VolunteerMatch. Greg joined the founding team in 1998 as its Chief Imagination Officer. Today, Greg oversees the expansion of a network that is already serving 100,000+ nonprofits, 150+ enterprise clients, and a quarter of a million interested volunteers a week.</div>  </div>  </div>\n    </div>\n  \n  \n  \n  \n      <div class=\"view-footer\">\n      <br>    </div>\n  \n  \n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"block-block-2\" class=\"block block-block last even\">\n\n      \n  <p><strong>How does the webinar work?</strong></p>\n<p>You attend the webinar using your Internet connection. Once you register, your confirmation email will provide you with an Internet link where you join the webinar at the specified date and time. The webinar audio uses your computer's microphone or speakers (VoIP). A telephone option is also available for audio. You will also be able to ask questions during the webinar.</p>\n<p><strong>System Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>PC based attendees - Windows 7, Vista XP or 2003 Server<br>Mac based attendees - Mac OS X 10.5 or newer</p>\n\n</div>\n              </div>\n            <div class=\"allclear\"></div>\n    </div><!-- /#content -->\n\n    \n          <aside class=\"sidebars\">\n                  <section class=\"about-workshop-text\">When it comes to talking about their businesses, many people are so close to their products or services they don’t know where to start. The StoryBrand Marketing Workshop helps companies understand what customers are looking for so they can tell their story in such a way people listen.</span><div id=\"livedesc-link-759\" class=\"sh-link livedesc-link sh-hide\"><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"showhide_toggle('livedesc', 759, 'Click to continue reading...', 'Click to hide text'); return false;\" aria-expanded=\"false\"><span id=\"livedesc-toggle-759\">Click to continue reading...</span></a></div><div id=\"livedesc-content-759\" class=\"sh-content livedesc-content sh-hide\" style=\"display: none;\">\n<p><span class=\"about-workshop-text\">We know how hard it is to communicate clearly and have helped hundreds of large and small businesses clarify their messaging. And when you clarify your message, your website starts working for you, your team members are converted into a sales force and your customers speak a viral message that spreads.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"about-workshop-text\">The StoryBrand Workshop is taught by Donald Miller, creator of the SB7 framework. Don has studied story for decades and as such is versatile in a language human beings have been speaking for centuries. Combined, his 7 books have spent more than a year on the NYT Bestsellers list. He’s consulted with hundreds of companies to help them clarify their messaging. Don isn’t a professor in an ivory tower. The SB7 framework was created to help him filter the messaging for his own company and the process resulted in him doubling revenue and profits for three consecutive years. Since then he’s gone on to consult with dozens of billion-dollar brands and hundreds of small businesses. Hundreds of Don’s clients have dramatically increased their revenue after learning the SB7 framework.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"about-workshop-text\">In the 2-day StoryBrand Workshop, you will: 1. Learn a proven communication formula that has been used in thousands of major motion pictures. You will completely understand how story works and why it’s the most powerful tool to compel a human brain. 2. See how this formula has been used by the world’s top brands in commercials, print ads and web-based marketing and 3. Apply this framework to your company’s messaging including websites, email blasts, keynotes and even elevator pitches. StoryBrand will help you create compelling messaging that stands out.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"about-workshop-text\">The human brain is drawn to CLARITY and away from confusion. If customers are confused about what you offer, they’ll look past you for somebody who can say it clearly. Once you clarify your message, your company will begin to grow. Companies that clarify their messaging win in the marketplace. Register for the StoryBrand Workshop today and spend 2 days with Donald Miller. Why? Because nobody will know how much they need your product or service until you tell them in the right way.</span><br>\n</p></div>\n<center><p></p>\n<p class=\"first\"><a href=\"#register\" class=\"button-green\">REGISTER NOW</a></p>\n</center></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"swiper-container swiper-container-testimonial swiper-container-horizontal\">\n<div class=\"swiper-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"swiper-slide swiper-slide-active\" data-video-src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/97231212?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;autoplay=true\" style=\"width: 785px;\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block dark\" style=\"background-image: url('/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/brian-bg.jpg'); background-color:#f1f1f1;min-height:600px;\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block-interior-quote-sales light\">\n<center><p></p>\n<p class=\"online-quote\"><em>“If you can clarify your message to the point where there’s that instant understanding and benefit that causes people to buy you’re never going to consider what the cost of this workshop was.”</em></p>\n<p class=\"online-quote-person\">BRIAN CLARK, CEO AND FOUNDER OF COPY BLOGGER</p>\n<p></p></center></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"swiper-slide for-desktop-only swiper-slide-next\" style=\"width: 785px;\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block dark\" style=\"background-image: url('/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/jmax-bg.jpg'); background-color:#f1f1f1;min-height:600px;\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block-interior-quote-sales light\">\n<center><p></p>\n<p class=\"online-quote\"><em>“Our business had grown fast and we needed a check-up on our branding strategy. background-color:none;\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block-interior light\" style=\"max-width:600px;\">\n<center><p></p>\n<div class=\"mobile-minus-margin\" style=\"margin-top:-180px;\">\n<div class=\"one-third first\">\n<a class=\"quote-circle\"><p></p>\n<div class=\"quote-circle quote-circle-brian\"><span class=\"play-quote\"></span></div>\n</a><p><a class=\"quote-circle\"></a>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"one-third for-desktop-only\">\n<a class=\"quote-circle\"><p></p>\n<div class=\"quote-circle quote-circle-john\"><span class=\"play-quote\"></span></div>\n</a><p><a class=\"quote-circle\"></a>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"one-third for-desktop-only\">\n<a class=\"quote-circle\"><p></p>\n<div class=\"quote-circle quote-circle-vik\"><span class=\"play-quote\"></span></div>\n</a><p><a class=\"quote-circle\"></a>\n</p></div>\n</div>\n<p></p></center><p></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n<div class=\"full-width-block dark\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff\" id=\"cost\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block-interior\" style=\"padding-top:40px\">\n<center><span class=\"online-title\">WHAT’S MY INVESTMENT?</span></center><p></p>\n<p class=\"two-thirds-center center\" style=\"font-size:.9em; padding-bottom:20px;\">How much is unclear messaging costing you? How many potential customers can’t hear your offer in the sea of noise? How many of your events are half empty because people don’t know why they should come? How many people are passing up your consulting? Can potential customers understand why they need your product or service? A lack of clarity may already be costing you a great deal.</p>\n<div class=\"one-third first\">\n<div class=\"price-container center\" align=\"center\"><span class=\"cost-headline\">One Registration</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-cost\">2,995</span><span class=\"workshop-each\"><br>\nper person</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-value\">&nbsp;</span><p></p>\n<p><a href=\"#register\" class=\"button-green\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\">REGISTER NOW</a></p></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n<div class=\"price-container center\" align=\"center\"><span class=\"cost-headline\">Two Registrations</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-cost\">2,895</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-each\">per person</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-value\">Total of $5,790</span><p></p>\n<p><a href=\"#register\" class=\"button-green\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\">REGISTER NOW</a></p></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n<div class=\"price-container center\" align=\"center\"><span class=\"cost-headline\">Three Registrations</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-cost\">2,795</span><span class=\"workshop-each\"><br>\nper person</span><br>\n<span class=\"workshop-value\">Total of $8,385</span><p></p>\n<p><a href=\"#register\" class=\"button-green\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\">REGISTER NOW</a></p></div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:18px;\"><center><em>*registration fee does not include hotel accommodations</em></center></div>\n<p class=\"center call-us first\" style=\"padding-bottom:20px;\">Have questions? &nbsp;<i class=\"fa fa-phone\"><span style=\"color:transparent;display:none;\">icon-phone</span></i>&nbsp; 615-915-1541</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"full-width-block\" style=\"background-image: url('none'); background-color:#3b3c48;\">\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n<div class=\"two-wide-container first\" style=\"background-color:#3b3c48;\">\n<div class=\"two-wide-interior\">\n<p class=\"two-wide-title\" style=\"color:#fff;\">Need a course designed to fit your team?</p>\n<p class=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:0px;\"><a href=\"https://storybrand.com/privateworkshops/\" class=\"online-button\" target=\"_blank\">GET A PRIVATE WORKSHOP</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two-wide-container\" style=\"background-color:#4e4f5d;float:right;\">\n<div class=\"two-wide-interior\">\n<p class=\"two-wide-title\" style=\"color:#fff;\">Looking for StoryBrand Certification?</p>\n<p class=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:0px;\"><a href=\"https://storybrand.com/guide/\" class=\"online-button\" target=\"_blank\">BECOME A GUIDE</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n<div class=\"full-width-block light section-green-bg\" id=\"schedule\">\n<div class=\"full-width-block-interior\">\n<center><span class=\"online-title\" style=\"color:#fff\">SCHEDULE</span></center><p></p>\n<div class=\"two-thirds-center\">\n<div class=\"tabs\">\n<ul class=\"tab-links\">\n<li class=\"active\"><a href=\"#tab1\">Sunday</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#tab2\">Monday</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#tab3\">Tuesday</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"tab-content top-pad\">\n<div id=\"tab1\" class=\"tab active\">\n<h3>Sunday</h3>\n<hr class=\"hr-big\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">8:00PM – Welcome Reception</span><br>\nYou’ll get to know your fellow participants over desserts and drinks. These are the like-minded leaders you’ll spend the next two days with. You’ll be inspired and encouraged by the brilliant friends who attend a StoryBrand workshop. At some point during the reception, Don will introduce the 7-part framework and set the stage for the two days ahead.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"tab2\" class=\"tab\">\n<h3>Monday</h3>\n<hr class=\"hr-big\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">9:00AM — Session One:<br>\nHow Learning to Tell a Great Story Will Grow Your Business</span><br>\nDon will break down a major Hollywood film showing you the tools screenwriters use to captivate an audience, and captivating an audience is exactly what your brand needs to do. The emphasis here is on clarity. If your brand can tell a better story than your competition, you’ll win in the marketplace. This 7-part framework will provide a filter for all your brand communication moving forward and it has been hiding under your nose all your life. Every time you watch a movie, from here on out, you’ll notice the tools screenwriters use to create clarity and to captivate an audience. You’ll use these tools to explain your ideas, products and services for the rest of your life. Telling a clear story will give you a distinct advantage.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">10:30AM – Session Two:<br>\nHow Successful Brands Use Story to Stay on Top</span><br>\nSuccessful brands are already using the StoryBrand framework. Whether they’re a small company, a billion-dollar brand or even a political candidate, the StoryBrand framework is the key to standing out against the competition. How did Domino’s Pizza mount their comeback? Why did Mitt Romney lose the election to Barack Obama? It will all become clear, and you’ll take furious notes about all the ways you can apply the framework to your brand.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">12:00PM – Lunch</span><br>\nGrab lunch with a fellow participant and be inspired by the work they are doing and their passion for their business. Turns out you’re not alone in trying to grow your company. These are relationships you will likely keep for years to come.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">1:30PM – Session Three:<br>\nKnowing Your Customer&nbsp;(With Work Groups)</span><br>\nMost brands position themselves as the hero in the story. But this never works. Your brand is the guide to the hero and we explain why. Every human being feels like they are the hero in the story, and successful brands affirm this identity in their customers and provide guidance so the hero can win the day. This paradigm shift alone will change the way you talk about your products and services forevermore.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">3:00PM – Session Four:<br>\nWhat Does Your Customer Really Want?&nbsp;(With Work Groups)</span><br>\nEvery customer wants something as it relates to your brand, but it’s not what you think. Businesses tend to sell solutions to external problems, but did you know customers tend to buy solutions to internal problems? In other words, customers are trying to resolve a frustration they’re feeling and you are going to be the brand that helps them resolve it. In this session, we will show you what customers are really looking for and once you start selling to that, you’ll start seeing an uptick in engagement and revenue.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">5:00PM – Done for the Day</span><br>\nGrab fellow participants for a night on the town and continue building your new community of like-minded professionals.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"tab3\" class=\"tab\">\n<h3>Tuesday</h3>\n<hr class=\"hr-big\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">9:00AM – Session Five:<br>\nBecoming the Guide</span><br>\nIn a story and in successful brand strategies, companies position themselves as the guide. Communication expert Nancy Duarte points out that leaders should position themselves as Yoda to Luke Skywalker or Haymitch to Katniss. To position your company as a guide, you need to do 2 magical things. We’ll explain what they are and how to do them in this session. And when you execute this strategy, you’ll be amazed at how you suddenly become the “brand” customers have been looking for.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">10:30AM – Session Six:<br>\nOffering a Plan</span><br>\nToo many companies rush into the room and try to sell their products. But remember, buying a product is a journey. And it can be a scary one, depending on what you’re selling and how expensive it is. When you offer 1 of the 3 kinds of plans we outline in this session, your customers will have much more confidence that you understand them and can help them resolve their problems. These plans have been working for successful companies for years and they will work for you, too.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">12:00PM – Lunch</span></p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">1:30PM – Session Seven:<br>\nCreating Your BrandScript</span><br>\nDuring session seven, we take all that you’ve learned, discussed, interacted with and brainstormed for the last 2 days and create a BrandScript for your brand. You will use this BrandScript in your e-mail blasts, on your website, in your advertising and even while talking to people at parties. Because your brand now has a clear story, people will understand you and word will start to spread.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">3:00PM – Session Eight:<br>\nImplementing Your BrandScript (Extended Session)</span><br>\nIn the final session, we critique your current marketing material. We actually put many of the Workshop attendees’ websites on an enormous television screen and talk about what needs to change. After all you’ve learned over the last few days, you’ll even be able to critique them yourself. What should your website say? What shouldn’t it say? Where are you confusing customers? Do they understand what your brand offers? Does what you offer resolve their internal conflict? Can the whole pitch be digested in just a few seconds, or are you rambling on? In this session, we will also show you how to write the perfect sales letter using the StoryBrand framework. This sales letter alone may pay for the cost of the entire workshop.</p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><span class=\"sc-title\">5:00PM – Workshop Concludes</span></p>\n<hr class=\"hr-schedule\">\n<p><em>*The StoryBrand Workshop includes 15 hours of lectures, plenty of time for interaction with Donald Miller and your peers, dozens of examples from Hollywood films and dozens more examples from web, print and television advertising. Each participant will also receive their own workbook containing more than a hundred pages of examples and inspiration from brands using story successfully. Experts in automated e-mail campaigns and copywriting will also be with us and you’ll get to ask plenty of questions about your own business. StoryBrand is the jolt of inspiration and information you need to fall back in love with doing business.</em></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><a name=\"register\"></a><a description</span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"g-cell g-cell-10-12 g-cell-md-1-1\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"label-primary\">Description</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"has-user-generated-content js-d-read-more read-more js-read-more read-more--medium-down read-more--expanded\" dorsal-guid=\"89a280b4-4b72-5b73-630c-36188c40c252\" data-xd-wired=\"read-more\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"js-xd-read-more-toggle-view read-more__toggle-view\" style=\"\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"js-xd-read-more-contents l-mar-top-3\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Emojicon</strong> is a multiple day celebration of all-things emoji that will take place November 4-6, 2016 in beautiful San Francisco.</p>\n<p>There will be lots of things to do! See emoji art. Watch emoji films. Discuss emoji policy. Learn how brands use emoji to communicate. Get your picture taken in an emoji photo booth. Eat emoji-themed food (including tacos from Taco Bell's emoji taco truck). Suggest new emoji to members of the Unicode Emoji Subcommittee.</p>\n<p>Mix. Mingle. Enjoy. </p>\n<p><strong>What's Happening</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Emojicon </strong>is meant to be accessible to everyone will have a wide range of activities, including</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Emoji Learn</strong>: a panel-and-workshop track</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Emoji Play</strong>: an emoji exhibitor space/art gallery<br></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Emoji Studio</strong>: an emoji hackathon and maker space<a href=\"http://emojipedia.org/keyboard/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\"><br></a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Emoji Film</strong>: an emoji film festival </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Emoji Party</strong>: an emoji opening night party (featuring only food that also are emoji).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Speakers include a curator from MoMA, the founder of Emojipedia, members of the Unicode Emoji Subcommittee, the author of the hijab emoji proposal and many notable designers.</p>\n<p>Emojicon has a wide variety of tickets, starting as low as $10, to welcome all levels of emoji love!</p>\n<p>Note: the main conference on Saturday and Sunday is at Westfield Mall. But the opening party is at Covo, at 981 Mission, near 6th Street.</p>\n<p><span>For more details, and the schedule, visit us at </span><a href=\"http://www.emojicon.co/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">emojicon.co</a><span>.</span></p>\n<p><br></p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"js-xd-read-more-toggle-director read-more__toggle-director l-pad-bot-4 l-sm-pad-bot-3\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript://\" class=\"read-more__more\" data-read-type=\"ReadMore\" data-checkpoint-name=\"read_more\">Read more</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"javascript://\" class=\"read-more__less\" data-read-type=\"ReadLess\" data-checkpoint-name=\"read_less\">Read }\n\t\t\t</style>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<!--webinarRegistrationForm ends-->  \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<!--webinarButtons\n\t\t\t<ul class=\"webinarButtons\">\n\t\t\t\t<li style=\"margin-left:0px;\"><a href=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/#\"><img src=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/images/iconAsk.png\"></a>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><a href=\"#\">Ask a Question</a></p></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"webinarSocialMedia\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"clearAll\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>        \n\t\t\t<div class=\"clearAll\"></div>\n\t\t\twebinarButtons ends-->        \n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<!--webinarThreeCols-->\n        <div id=\"webinarColumns\">\n  \t\t<div class=\"webinarThreeColsLeft\">\n        \t<h2 class=\"color_font_pharma\">Translation from Bench to Bedside, and Back</h2>\n            <p>Drug-induced kidney injury continues to be an obstacle in the development of novel and safe drugs. This area has become even more complicated by the recognition of the need for kidney-targeted medications for diseases such as Chronic Kidney Disease and Diabetes. Classic biomarkers for drug-induced kidney injury, serum creatinine and urea nitrogen (BUN) are relatively insensitive and nonspecific in human patients and nonclinical species. Therefore, in drug development, novel biomarkers with improved sensitivity, as compared to BUN and creatinine concentrations, are needed for identification and characterization of kidney injury in nonclinical species and human patients. Novel translational biomarkers of drug-induced kidney injury in rats have been identified, developed and qualified by ongoing efforts through private-public partnerships. These translational biomarkers are being used to improve safety monitoring in nonclinical and clinical trials with the goal of attrition during the drug development process.<br>\n<br>\nThis webinar will provide an overview of translational biomarkers of kidney injury in rats that have been successfully qualified for the identification of drug-induced kidney injury in nonclinical studies. Featured biomarkers in this webinar will include examples of translational urinary biomarkers of tubular injury/induced synthesis (e.g., KIM-1 and clusterin), altered tubular function (e.g., cystatin C, microglobulins), glomerular injury (e.g., microalbumin, cystatin C, microglobulins) or production by inflammatory cells (e.g.,neutrophil gelatinase-associated lipocalin [NGAL]). Topics incorporated as part of this introduction to these translational biomarkers will include response to classic nephrotoxicants, correlation with histopathology findings, localization of biomarkers in the nephron and considerations for interpretation of biomarker data in rodent and non-rodent nonclinical studies.<br>\n<br>\nThis webinar is intended to introduce the participant to novel and emerging biomarkers of kidney injury that provide exciting opportunities to bridge nonclinical and clinical trials in the development of new therapeutic entities. Implementation of translational biomarker strategies in drug development provides opportunities to investigate efficacy in disease models, tools for identification of kidney injury in preclinical studies and safety endpoints for clinical studies.</p>\n        </div><!--left ends-->\n        \n        <div class=\"webinarThreeColsMiddle\" style=\"height: 1385px;\">\n        \t<h2 class=\"color_font_pharma\">Presented by</h2>            \n            <img src=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/images/speakers/YwvpMdcg.jpg\" class=\"speaker\"><h3>Michael D. Cressman, DO,</h3>\n\t\t\t\t<h4>Senior Medical Director, CVMER (cardiovascular, metabolic, endocrine, renal) Group</h4>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Michael Cressman is a board certified nephrologist who has over 30 years of experience in clinical trials for cardiovascular, metabolic and renal disorders.  <br>\n<br>\nHe is a former member of the professional staff of the Cleveland Clinic, associate professor of Medicine in the Center for Clinical Pharmacology at the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center and was chair of the Renal Safety Knowledge Group at AstraZeneca.  His prior experience includes numerous interactions with the FDA and other regulatory agencies on a wide range of renal-related issues that are relevant to the clinical development process.  Dr. Cressman joined Covance as a senior medical director in 2012. </p>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tenPix\"></div><img src=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/images/speakers/R2vXLC4K.jpg\" class=\"speaker\"><h3>Laura I Boone, DVM, PhD, Diplomate, ACVP, DABT,</h3>\n\t\t\t\t<h4>Scientific Director of Clinical Pathology for Europe, Nonclinical Development, Covance Laboratories, Inc</h4>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Dr. Boone attended Texas A&amp;M University where she received her BS, DVM, and PhD, and completed her clinical pathology residency. She has board certification from the American College of Veterinary Pathology (Clinical Pathology) and American Board of Toxicology (ABT). She currently serves as the scientific director of Clinical Pathology for Covance sites in Muenster, Germany and Harrogate, England.  Prior to joining Covance, she was a project pathologist and toxicologist with Eli Lilly. Dr. Boone has been published in peer reviewed journals and presented at national and international pathology and toxicology meetings. Her areas of expertise and interest include clinical pathology and renal, hepatic, and hematopoietic toxicology.</p>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tenPix\"></div><img src=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/images/speakers/rFwqC4QZ.jpg\" class=\"speaker\"><h3>Katherine T Landschulz, PhD,</h3>\n\t\t\t\t<h4>Associate Director, Translational Biomarker Solutions, Covance Laboratories, Inc.</h4>\n\t\t\t\t<p>Dr. Landschulz received her BSc in Genetics from the University of California, Davis, and Ph.D. from Johns Hopkins University, Program in Human Genetics. She first joined the pharmaceutical industry in 1997 after completing postdoctoral training at Johns Hopkins University and the University of Texas, Southwestern Medical Center. At Pfizer, and then subsequently Abbott and Eli Lilly, Dr. Landschulz held a variety of roles in Discovery through Translational Medicine. Dr. Landschulz initially joined the Covance Biomarker laboratory in 2010 as principal scientist for Cardiovascular/Metabolic Disease Biomarkers. Since 2015, as Associate Director, Dr. Landschulz has managed and supervised all TBS biomarker services, including Immunoassay/Special Chemistry, Cell Biology/Flow Cytometry, and Clinical Pathology laboratories, and continues to guide biomarker selection and feasibility/validation consultation for the Cardiovascular/Metabolic Disease therapeutic area. </p>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tenPix\"></div>            \n        </div><!--middle ends-->\n        \n\t\t<div class=\"webinarThreeColsRight\">\n        \t<a href=\"http://www.\" title=\"Covance\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.business-review-webinars.com/images/logos/vxY4gKC1.jpg\" class=\"Companylogo\"></a>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n   \t  \t\t\n            <!--<h2 class=\"color_font_pharma\">Related Materials</h2>\n      \t\t<a href=\"<?= ROOT; ?>#\"><img src=\"<?= ROOT; ?>images/iconPDF.jpg\" class=\"webinarPDF\"></a>\n            <p><a href=\"<?= ROOT; ?>#\">Download</a> our whitepaper on distribution and certification</p> \n            <div class=\"clearAll\"></div>-->\n                       \n            <div class=\"tenPix\"></div>\n            \n            <h2 class=\"color_font_pharma\">Key Learning Objectives</h2>\n            <ul><li>Introduce translational novel biomarkers to bridge nonclinical studies and human patients</li><li>Provide an overview of successful translational biomarkers</li><li>Provide insight into evaluation of nonclinical urine biomarker data</li><li>Discuss translational biomarkers in clinical trials for recent renal-related diseases/mechanisms</li></ul>\n\t\t\t\n            <div class=\"tenPix\"></div>\n            \n            \n            <h2 class=\"color_font_pharma\">Audience</h2>\n            <ul><li>Chief
